BookingCreateRequest.description:
Booking creation happens in two stages for credit payment, for all others the second stage is irrelevant.

1. Send the booking info for the backend to create a booking, if the payment method is credit the response will contain an additional field “iframeHtml” with html for stripe form which can be directly rendered for users to input the credit card details and complete the payment.
2. The “iframHtml” value is directly rendered in an iframe. The rendered stripe form in iframe will handle the necessary steps for completing the payment and post a message back to the parent window with payment status, this can be used for user feedback in the frontend.

    window.addEventListener("message", function(event) { ... }

Following is the relevant info from the event object 

    {
      ...
      data: {
        type: "payment_success" // or "payment_error"
        message: "" // Error description if there was an error
      }
      ...
    }

Booking is successful when the “payment_success” message is received, until then the booking will be in “incomplete” status.

